# demo-builder — ai-chatbot-for-customer-support

All 12 files built and validated. Demo live at:
`/demos/ai-chatbot-for-customer-support/` (served from `michaelwegter.com/public/demos/ai-chatbot-for-customer-support/`)

---

## Files created

| File | Role |
|---|---|
| `index.html` | Customer-facing page: fake retail site shell + floating chat widget (auto-opens after 800ms) |
| `admin.html` | Admin panel: password-gated, 3-tab UI |
| `style.css` | Full design system: tokens, widget, bubbles, escalation cards, admin, responsive |
| `chat.js` | Main orchestrator: RAG -> LLM -> render; escalation intent detection; order lookup; typing indicators |
| `model-loader.js` | 3-tier chain: WebGPU (WebLLM Llama-3.2-1B) -> WASM (Qwen2.5-0.5B-Instruct via @huggingface/transformers@4.2.0) -> template-RAG |
| `rag.js` | Cosine-sim retrieval over pre-embedded FAQ corpus; keyword fallback pre-warmup; system-prompt builder |
| `order-api.js` | orders.json lookup by ORD-XXXXX or email; regex extractor for user messages |
| `escalation.js` | ET hours detection (Intl API, Mon-Fri 9am-6pm); escalation form HTML; ticket confirmation card |
| `admin.js` | Analytics dashboard (6 stat cards, top queries, events log), KB editor (add/edit/delete entries), session viewer |
| `analytics.js` | sessionStorage event bus; getStats() for dashboard; 7 event types |
| `knowledge-base.json` | 20-entry FAQ corpus (Orders, Shipping, Returns, Payments, Issues, Promotions, Support) |
| `orders.json` | 10 mock orders; lookup by ORD-ID or email |

## workSamples.js

Entry added as `id: 11`, `slug: "ai-chatbot-for-customer-support"`.

## Feature coverage

- **RAG**: embedding-based cosine sim (Xenova/all-MiniLM-L6-v2) with keyword fallback pre-warmup; top-3 retrieval; source citation badge when score > 0.3
- **Order lookup**: regex detects ORD-XXXXX or email in any message; injects result into system prompt context; logs `order_lookup` event
- **3-tier LLM**: WebGPU (WebLLM, ~600-900 MB VRAM) -> WASM Qwen2.5-0.5B-Instruct q4 -> template-RAG verbatim answer; progress bar with tier badge during load
- **Escalation**: keyword/intent detection (human/agent/complaint etc.); ET business hours check; inline form; Zendesk ticket card with simulated TKT-XXXXX ID
- **Admin**: password-gated (demo: admin123); analytics tab (deflection rate, top queries, event log, clear); KB tab (add/edit/delete entries with live corpus update); sessions tab (event log grouped by sessionId; refreshes every 5s)
- **Accessibility**: role="dialog", aria-live="polite", aria-label on all interactive elements, Escape key closes panel
- **Mobile**: full-screen panel at <480px
- **Design**: clean SaaS/tech palette (--blue #1D6AE5, --dark #0F172A, Inter); Zendesk-style widget UI; no michaelwegter.com tokens

## Validation

- All JSON: valid (node parse)
- All JS: syntax clean (node --check)
- Zero build step, zero npm, native ESM modules

---

## handoff
- produced: 12-file self-contained demo at `public/demos/ai-chatbot-for-customer-support/`; workSamples.js entry added as id:11; all JS syntax clean, both JSON valid
- decisions: WASM Qwen2.5-0.5B-Instruct is primary path; WebGPU is progressive enhancement; template-RAG is Tier 3 fallback; no backend required; admin password is "admin123" (demo-only)
- next needs: deploy step pushes `michaelwegter.com` to GitHub Pages; verify `/demos/ai-chatbot-for-customer-support/` returns 200; note that first WASM load is 30-60s (cached in IndexedDB after)
- risks: WASM model download (~300-500 MB) may timeout in CI headless; template-RAG fallback ensures demo always functions without LLM; `@huggingface/transformers@4.2.0` pipeline output shape (`out[0].generated_text.at(-1).content`) validated against spec but not live-tested in headless yet
